 39class _Dialect(type):
 40    classes: t.Dict[str, Dialect] = {}
 41
 42    @classmethod
 43    def __getitem__(cls, key):
 44        return cls.classes[key]
 45
 46    @classmethod
 47    def get(cls, key, default=None):
 48        return cls.classes.get(key, default)
 49
 50    def __new__(cls, clsname, bases, attrs):
 51        klass = super().__new__(cls, clsname, bases, attrs)
 52        enum = Dialects.__members__.get(clsname.upper())
 53        cls.classes[enum.value if enum is not None else clsname.lower()] = klass
 54
 55        klass.time_trie = new_trie(klass.time_mapping)
 56        klass.inverse_time_mapping = {v: k for k, v in klass.time_mapping.items()}
 57        klass.inverse_time_trie = new_trie(klass.inverse_time_mapping)
 58
 59        klass.tokenizer_class = getattr(klass, "Tokenizer", Tokenizer)
 60        klass.parser_class = getattr(klass, "Parser", Parser)
 61        klass.generator_class = getattr(klass, "Generator", Generator)
 62
 63        klass.quote_start, klass.quote_end = list(klass.tokenizer_class._QUOTES.items())[0]
 64        klass.identifier_start, klass.identifier_end = list(
 65            klass.tokenizer_class._IDENTIFIERS.items()
 66        )[0]
 67
 68        if (
 69            klass.tokenizer_class._BIT_STRINGS
 70            and exp.BitString not in klass.generator_class.TRANSFORMS
 71        ):
 72            bs_start, bs_end = list(klass.tokenizer_class._BIT_STRINGS.items())[0]
 73            klass.generator_class.TRANSFORMS[
 74                exp.BitString
 75            ] = lambda self, e: f"{bs_start}{int(self.sql(e, 'this')):b}{bs_end}"
 76        if (
 77            klass.tokenizer_class._HEX_STRINGS
 78            and exp.HexString not in klass.generator_class.TRANSFORMS
 79        ):
 80            hs_start, hs_end = list(klass.tokenizer_class._HEX_STRINGS.items())[0]
 81            klass.generator_class.TRANSFORMS[
 82                exp.HexString
 83            ] = lambda self, e: f"{hs_start}{int(self.sql(e, 'this')):X}{hs_end}"
 84        if (
 85            klass.tokenizer_class._BYTE_STRINGS
 86            and exp.ByteString not in klass.generator_class.TRANSFORMS
 87        ):
 88            be_start, be_end = list(klass.tokenizer_class._BYTE_STRINGS.items())[0]
 89            klass.generator_class.TRANSFORMS[
 90                exp.ByteString
 91            ] = lambda self, e: f"{be_start}{self.sql(e, 'this')}{be_end}"
 92
 93        return klass

 96class Dialect(metaclass=_Dialect):
 97    index_offset = 0
 98    unnest_column_only = False
 99    alias_post_tablesample = False
100    normalize_functions: t.Optional[str] = "upper"
101    null_ordering = "nulls_are_small"
102
103    date_format = "'%Y-%m-%d'"
104    dateint_format = "'%Y%m%d'"
105    time_format = "'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'"
106    time_mapping: t.Dict[str, str] = {}
107
108    # autofilled
109    quote_start = None
110    quote_end = None
111    identifier_start = None
112    identifier_end = None
113
114    time_trie = None
115    inverse_time_mapping = None
116    inverse_time_trie = None
117    tokenizer_class = None
118    parser_class = None
119    generator_class = None
120
121    @classmethod
122    def get_or_raise(cls, dialect):
123        if not dialect:
124            return cls
125        if isinstance(dialect, _Dialect):
126            return dialect
127        if isinstance(dialect, Dialect):
128            return dialect.__class__
129
130        result = cls.get(dialect)
131        if not result:
132            raise ValueError(f"Unknown dialect '{dialect}'")
133
134        return result
135
136    @classmethod
137    def format_time(cls, expression):
138        if isinstance(expression, str):
139            return exp.Literal.string(
140                format_time(
141                    expression[1:-1],  # the time formats are quoted
142                    cls.time_mapping,
143                    cls.time_trie,
144                )
145            )
146        if expression and expression.is_string:
147            return exp.Literal.string(
148                format_time(
149                    expression.this,
150                    cls.time_mapping,
151                    cls.time_trie,
152                )
153            )
154        return expression
155
156    def parse(self, sql, **opts):
157        return self.parser(**opts).parse(self.tokenizer.tokenize(sql), sql)
158
159    def parse_into(self, expression_type, sql, **opts):
160        return self.parser(**opts).parse_into(expression_type, self.tokenizer.tokenize(sql), sql)
161
162    def generate(self, expression, **opts):
163        return self.generator(**opts).generate(expression)
164
165    def transpile(self, code, **opts):
166        return self.generate(self.parse(code), **opts)
167
168    @property
169    def tokenizer(self):
170        if not hasattr(self, "_tokenizer"):
171            self._tokenizer = self.tokenizer_class()
172        return self._tokenizer
173
174    def parser(self, **opts):
175        return self.parser_class(
176            **{
177                "index_offset": self.index_offset,
178                "unnest_column_only": self.unnest_column_only,
179                "alias_post_tablesample": self.alias_post_tablesample,
180                "null_ordering": self.null_ordering,
181                **opts,
182            },
183        )
184
185    def generator(self, **opts):
186        return self.generator_class(
187            **{
188                "quote_start": self.quote_start,
189                "quote_end": self.quote_end,
190                "identifier_start": self.identifier_start,
191                "identifier_end": self.identifier_end,
192                "escape": self.tokenizer_class.ESCAPES[0],
193                "index_offset": self.index_offset,
194                "time_mapping": self.inverse_time_mapping,
195                "time_trie": self.inverse_time_trie,
196                "unnest_column_only": self.unnest_column_only,
197                "alias_post_tablesample": self.alias_post_tablesample,
198                "normalize_functions": self.normalize_functions,
199                "null_ordering": self.null_ordering,
200                **opts,
201            }
202        )

209def rename_func(name):
210    def _rename(self, expression):
211        args = flatten(expression.args.values())
212        return f"{self.normalize_func(name)}({self.format_args(*args)})"
213
214    return _rename

288def str_position_sql(self, expression):
289    this = self.sql(expression, "this")
290    substr = self.sql(expression, "substr")
291    position = self.sql(expression, "position")
292    if position:
293        return f"STRPOS(SUBSTR({this}, {position}), {substr}) + {position} - 1"
294    return f"STRPOS({this}, {substr})"

297def struct_extract_sql(self, expression):
298    this = self.sql(expression, "this")
299    struct_key = self.sql(exp.Identifier(this=expression.expression, quoted=True))
300    return f"{this}.{struct_key}"

303def var_map_sql(self, expression, map_func_name="MAP"):
304    keys = expression.args["keys"]
305    values = expression.args["values"]
306
307    if not isinstance(keys, exp.Array) or not isinstance(values, exp.Array):
308        self.unsupported("Cannot convert array columns into map.")
309        return f"{map_func_name}({self.format_args(keys, values)})"
310
311    args = []
312    for key, value in zip(keys.expressions, values.expressions):
313        args.append(self.sql(key))
314        args.append(self.sql(value))
315    return f"{map_func_name}({self.format_args(*args)})"

318def format_time_lambda(exp_class, dialect, default=None):
319    """Helper used for time expressions.
320
321    Args
322        exp_class (Class): the expression class to instantiate
323        dialect (string): sql dialect
324        default (Option[bool | str]): the default format, True being time
325    """
326
327    def _format_time(args):
328        return exp_class(
329            this=seq_get(args, 0),
330            format=Dialect[dialect].format_time(
331                seq_get(args, 1) or (Dialect[dialect].time_format if default is True else default)
332            ),
333        )
334
335    return _format_time

338def create_with_partitions_sql(self, expression):
339    """
340    In Hive and Spark, the PARTITIONED BY property acts as an extension of a table's schema. When the
341    PARTITIONED BY value is an array of column names, they are transformed into a schema. The corresponding
342    columns are removed from the create statement.
343    """
344    has_schema = isinstance(expression.this, exp.Schema)
345    is_partitionable = expression.args.get("kind") in ("TABLE", "VIEW")
346
347    if has_schema and is_partitionable:
348        expression = expression.copy()
349        prop = expression.find(exp.PartitionedByProperty)
350        this = prop and prop.this
351        if prop and not isinstance(this, exp.Schema):
352            schema = expression.this
353            columns = {v.name.upper() for v in this.expressions}
354            partitions = [col for col in schema.expressions if col.name.upper() in columns]
355            schema.set("expressions", [e for e in schema.expressions if e not in partitions])
356            prop.replace(exp.PartitionedByProperty(this=exp.Schema(expressions=partitions)))
357            expression.set("this", schema)
358
359    return self.create_sql(expression)

362def parse_date_delta(exp_class, unit_mapping=None):
363    def inner_func(args):
364        unit_based = len(args) == 3
365        this = seq_get(args, 2) if unit_based else seq_get(args, 0)
366        expression = seq_get(args, 1) if unit_based else seq_get(args, 1)
367        unit = seq_get(args, 0) if unit_based else exp.Literal.string("DAY")
368        unit = unit_mapping.get(unit.name.lower(), unit) if unit_mapping else unit
369        return exp_class(this=this, expression=expression, unit=unit)
370
371    return inner_func

397def trim_sql(self, expression):
398    target = self.sql(expression, "this")
399    trim_type = self.sql(expression, "position")
400    remove_chars = self.sql(expression, "expression")
401    collation = self.sql(expression, "collation")
402
403    # Use TRIM/LTRIM/RTRIM syntax if the expression isn't database-specific
404    if not remove_chars and not collation:
405        return self.trim_sql(expression)
406
407    trim_type = f"{trim_type} " if trim_type else ""
408    remove_chars = f"{remove_chars} " if remove_chars else ""
409    from_part = "FROM " if trim_type or remove_chars else ""
410    collation = f" COLLATE {collation}" if collation else ""
411    return f"TRIM({trim_type}{remove_chars}{from_part}{target}{collation})"

 387class Tokenizer(metaclass=_Tokenizer):
 388    SINGLE_TOKENS = {
 389        "(": TokenType.L_PAREN,
 390        ")": TokenType.R_PAREN,
 391        "[": TokenType.L_BRACKET,
 392        "]": TokenType.R_BRACKET,
 393        "{": TokenType.L_BRACE,
 394        "}": TokenType.R_BRACE,
 395        "&": TokenType.AMP,
 396        "^": TokenType.CARET,

 747    def __init__(self) -> None:
 748        self._replace_backslash = "\\" in self._ESCAPES
 749        self.reset()
 750
 751    def reset(self) -> None:
 752        self.sql = ""
 753        self.size = 0
 754        self.tokens: t.List[Token] = []
 755        self._start = 0
 756        self._current = 0
 757        self._line = 1
 758        self._col = 1
 759        self._comments: t.List[str] = []
 760
 761        self._char = None
 762        self._end = None
 763        self._peek = None
 764        self._prev_token_line = -1
 765        self._prev_token_comments: t.List[str] = []
 766        self._prev_token_type = None
 767
 768    def tokenize(self, sql: str) -> t.List[Token]:
 769        """Returns a list of tokens corresponding to the SQL string `sql`."""
 770        self.reset()
 771        self.sql = sql
 772        self.size = len(sql)
 773        self._scan()
 774        return self.tokens
 775
 776    def _scan(self, until: t.Optional[t.Callable] = None) -> None:
 777        while self.size and not self._end:
 778            self._start = self._current
 779            self._advance()
 780
 781            if not self._char:
 782                break
 783
 784            white_space = self.WHITE_SPACE.get(self._char)  # type: ignore
 785            identifier_end = self._IDENTIFIERS.get(self._char)  # type: ignore
 786
 787            if white_space:
 788                if white_space == TokenType.BREAK:
 789                    self._col = 1
 790                    self._line += 1
 791            elif self._char.isdigit():  # type:ignore
 792                self._scan_number()
 793            elif identifier_end:
 794                self._scan_identifier(identifier_end)
 795            else:
 796                self._scan_keywords()
 797
 798            if until and until():
 799                break
 800
 801    def _chars(self, size: int) -> str:
 802        if size == 1:
 803            return self._char  # type: ignore
 804        start = self._current - 1
 805        end = start + size
 806        if end <= self.size:
 807            return self.sql[start:end]
 808        return ""
 809
 810    def _advance(self, i: int = 1) -> None:
 811        self._col += i
 812        self._current += i
 813        self._end = self._current >= self.size  # type: ignore
 814        self._char = self.sql[self._current - 1]  # type: ignore
 815        self._peek = self.sql[self._current] if self._current < self.size else ""  # type: ignore
 816
 817    @property
 818    def _text(self) -> str:
 819        return self.sql[self._start : self._current]
 820
 821    def _add(self, token_type: TokenType, text: t.Optional[str] = None) -> None:
 822        self._prev_token_line = self._line
 823        self._prev_token_comments = self._comments
 824        self._prev_token_type = token_type  # type: ignore
 825        self.tokens.append(
 826            Token(
 827                token_type,
 828                self._text if text is None else text,
 829                self._line,
 830                self._col,
 831                self._comments,
 832            )
 833        )
 834        self._comments = []
 835
 836        # If we have either a semicolon or a begin token before the command's token, we'll parse
 837        # whatever follows the command's token as a string
 838        if token_type in self.COMMANDS and (
 839            len(self.tokens) == 1 or self.tokens[-2].token_type in self.COMMAND_PREFIX_TOKENS
 840        ):
 841            start = self._current
 842            tokens = len(self.tokens)
 843            self._scan(lambda: self._peek == ";")
 844            self.tokens = self.tokens[:tokens]
 845            text = self.sql[start : self._current].strip()
 846            if text:
 847                self._add(TokenType.STRING, text)
 848
 849    def _scan_keywords(self) -> None:
 850        size = 0
 851        word = None
 852        chars = self._text
 853        char = chars
 854        prev_space = False
 855        skip = False
 856        trie = self.KEYWORD_TRIE
 857
 858        while chars:
 859            if skip:
 860                result = 1
 861            else:
 862                result, trie = in_trie(trie, char.upper())  # type: ignore
 863
 864            if result == 0:
 865                break
 866            if result == 2:
 867                word = chars
 868            size += 1
 869            end = self._current - 1 + size
 870
 871            if end < self.size:
 872                char = self.sql[end]
 873                is_space = char in self.WHITE_SPACE
 874
 875                if not is_space or not prev_space:
 876                    if is_space:
 877                        char = " "
 878                    chars += char
 879                    prev_space = is_space
 880                    skip = False
 881                else:
 882                    skip = True
 883            else:
 884                chars = None  # type: ignore
 885
 886        if not word:
 887            if self._char in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
 888                self._add(self.SINGLE_TOKENS[self._char])  # type: ignore
 889                return
 890            self._scan_var()
 891            return
 892
 893        if self._scan_string(word):
 894            return
 895        if self._scan_formatted_string(word):
 896            return
 897        if self._scan_comment(word):
 898            return
 899
 900        self._advance(size - 1)
 901        self._add(self.KEYWORDS[word.upper()])
 902
 903    def _scan_comment(self, comment_start: str) -> bool:
 904        if comment_start not in self._COMMENTS:  # type: ignore
 905            return False
 906
 907        comment_start_line = self._line
 908        comment_start_size = len(comment_start)
 909        comment_end = self._COMMENTS[comment_start]  # type: ignore
 910
 911        if comment_end:
 912            comment_end_size = len(comment_end)
 913
 914            while not self._end and self._chars(comment_end_size) != comment_end:
 915                self._advance()
 916
 917            self._comments.append(self._text[comment_start_size : -comment_end_size + 1])  # type: ignore
 918            self._advance(comment_end_size - 1)
 919        else:
 920            while not self._end and self.WHITE_SPACE.get(self._peek) != TokenType.BREAK:  # type: ignore
 921                self._advance()
 922            self._comments.append(self._text[comment_start_size:])  # type: ignore
 923
 924        # Leading comment is attached to the succeeding token, whilst trailing comment to the preceding.
 925        # Multiple consecutive comments are preserved by appending them to the current comments list.
 926        if comment_start_line == self._prev_token_line:
 927            self.tokens[-1].comments.extend(self._comments)
 928            self._comments = []
 929
 930        return True
 931
 932    def _scan_number(self) -> None:
 933        if self._char == "0":
 934            peek = self._peek.upper()  # type: ignore
 935            if peek == "B":
 936                return self._scan_bits()
 937            elif peek == "X":
 938                return self._scan_hex()
 939
 940        decimal = False
 941        scientific = 0
 942
 943        while True:
 944            if self._peek.isdigit():  # type: ignore
 945                self._advance()
 946            elif self._peek == "." and not decimal:
 947                decimal = True
 948                self._advance()
 949            elif self._peek in ("-", "+") and scientific == 1:
 950                scientific += 1
 951                self._advance()
 952            elif self._peek.upper() == "E" and not scientific:  # type: ignore
 953                scientific += 1
 954                self._advance()
 955            elif self._peek.isidentifier():  # type: ignore
 956                number_text = self._text
 957                literal = []
 958
 959                while self._peek.strip() and self._peek not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:  # type: ignore
 960                    literal.append(self._peek.upper())  # type: ignore
 961                    self._advance()
 962
 963                literal = "".join(literal)  # type: ignore
 964                token_type = self.KEYWORDS.get(self.NUMERIC_LITERALS.get(literal))  # type: ignore
 965
 966                if token_type:
 967                    self._add(TokenType.NUMBER, number_text)
 968                    self._add(TokenType.DCOLON, "::")
 969                    return self._add(token_type, literal)  # type: ignore
 970                elif self.IDENTIFIER_CAN_START_WITH_DIGIT:
 971                    return self._add(TokenType.VAR)
 972
 973                self._add(TokenType.NUMBER, number_text)
 974                return self._advance(-len(literal))
 975            else:
 976                return self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
 977
 978    def _scan_bits(self) -> None:
 979        self._advance()
 980        value = self._extract_value()
 981        try:
 982            self._add(TokenType.BIT_STRING, f"{int(value, 2)}")
 983        except ValueError:
 984            self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER)
 985
 986    def _scan_hex(self) -> None:
 987        self._advance()
 988        value = self._extract_value()
 989        try:
 990            self._add(TokenType.HEX_STRING, f"{int(value, 16)}")
 991        except ValueError:
 992            self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER)
 993
 994    def _extract_value(self) -> str:
 995        while True:
 996            char = self._peek.strip()  # type: ignore
 997            if char and char not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
 998                self._advance()
 999            else:
1000                break
1001
1002        return self._text
1003
1004    def _scan_string(self, quote: str) -> bool:
1005        quote_end = self._QUOTES.get(quote)  # type: ignore
1006        if quote_end is None:
1007            return False
1008
1009        self._advance(len(quote))
1010        text = self._extract_string(quote_end)
1011        text = text.encode(self.ENCODE).decode(self.ENCODE) if self.ENCODE else text  # type: ignore
1012        text = text.replace("\\\\", "\\") if self._replace_backslash else text
1013        self._add(TokenType.NATIONAL if quote[0].upper() == "N" else TokenType.STRING, text)
1014        return True
1015
1016    # X'1234, b'0110', E'\\\\\' etc.
1017    def _scan_formatted_string(self, string_start: str) -> bool:
1018        if string_start in self._HEX_STRINGS:  # type: ignore
1019            delimiters = self._HEX_STRINGS  # type: ignore
1020            token_type = TokenType.HEX_STRING
1021            base = 16
1022        elif string_start in self._BIT_STRINGS:  # type: ignore
1023            delimiters = self._BIT_STRINGS  # type: ignore
1024            token_type = TokenType.BIT_STRING
1025            base = 2
1026        elif string_start in self._BYTE_STRINGS:  # type: ignore
1027            delimiters = self._BYTE_STRINGS  # type: ignore
1028            token_type = TokenType.BYTE_STRING
1029            base = None
1030        else:
1031            return False
1032
1033        self._advance(len(string_start))
1034        string_end = delimiters.get(string_start)
1035        text = self._extract_string(string_end)
1036
1037        if base is None:
1038            self._add(token_type, text)
1039        else:
1040            try:
1041                self._add(token_type, f"{int(text, base)}")
1042            except:
1043                raise RuntimeError(
1044                    f"Numeric string contains invalid characters from {self._line}:{self._start}"
1045                )
1046
1047        return True
1048
1049    def _scan_identifier(self, identifier_end: str) -> None:
1050        while self._peek != identifier_end:
1051            if self._end:
1052                raise RuntimeError(f"Missing {identifier_end} from {self._line}:{self._start}")
1053            self._advance()
1054        self._advance()
1055        self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER, self._text[1:-1])
1056
1057    def _scan_var(self) -> None:
1058        while True:
1059            char = self._peek.strip()  # type: ignore
1060            if char and char not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
1061                self._advance()
1062            else:
1063                break
1064        self._add(
1065            TokenType.VAR
1066            if self._prev_token_type == TokenType.PARAMETER
1067            else self.KEYWORDS.get(self._text.upper(), TokenType.VAR)
1068        )
1069
1070    def _extract_string(self, delimiter: str) -> str:
1071        text = ""
1072        delim_size = len(delimiter)
1073
1074        while True:
1075            if (
1076                self._char in self._ESCAPES
1077                and self._peek
1078                and (self._peek == delimiter or self._peek in self._ESCAPES)
1079            ):
1080                text += self._peek
1081                self._advance(2)
1082            else:
1083                if self._chars(delim_size) == delimiter:
1084                    if delim_size > 1:
1085                        self._advance(delim_size - 1)
1086                    break
1087
1088                if self._end:
1089                    raise RuntimeError(f"Missing {delimiter} from {self._line}:{self._start}")
1090                text += self._char  # type: ignore
1091                self._advance()
1092
1093        return text

 661    def __init__(
 662        self,
 663        error_level: t.Optional[ErrorLevel] = None,
 664        error_message_context: int = 100,
 665        index_offset: int = 0,
 666        unnest_column_only: bool = False,
 667        alias_post_tablesample: bool = False,
 668        max_errors: int = 3,
 669        null_ordering: t.Optional[str] = None,
 670    ):
 671        self.error_level = error_level or ErrorLevel.IMMEDIATE
 672        self.error_message_context = error_message_context

 675        self.alias_post_tablesample = alias_post_tablesample

 680    def reset(self):
 681        self.sql = ""
 682        self.errors = []
 683        self._tokens = []
 684        self._index = 0
 685        self._curr = None
 686        self._next = None
 687        self._prev = None
 688        self._prev_comments = None

 690    def parse(
 691        self, raw_tokens: t.List[Token], sql: t.Optional[str] = None
 692    ) -> t.List[t.Optional[exp.Expression]]:
 693        """
 694        Parses a list of tokens and returns a list of syntax trees, one tree
 695        per parsed SQL statement.
 696
 697        Args:
 698            raw_tokens: the list of tokens.
 699            sql: the original SQL string, used to produce helpful debug messages.
 700
 701        Returns:
 702            The list of syntax trees.
 703        """
 704        return self._parse(
 705            parse_method=self.__class__._parse_statement, raw_tokens=raw_tokens, sql=sql
 706        )
 707
 708    def parse_into(
 709        self,
 710        expression_types: exp.IntoType,
 711        raw_tokens: t.List[Token],
 712        sql: t.Optional[str] = None,
 713    ) -> t.List[t.Optional[exp.Expression]]:
 714        """
 715        Parses a list of tokens into a given Expression type. If a collection of Expression
 716        types is given instead, this method will try to parse the token list into each one
 717        of them, stopping at the first for which the parsing succeeds.
 718
 719        Args:
 720            expression_types: the expression type(s) to try and parse the token list into.
 721            raw_tokens: the list of tokens.
 722            sql: the original SQL string, used to produce helpful debug messages.
 723
 724        Returns:
 725            The target Expression.
 726        """
 727        errors = []
 728        for expression_type in ensure_collection(expression_types):
 729            parser = self.EXPRESSION_PARSERS.get(expression_type)
 730            if not parser:
 731                raise TypeError(f"No parser registered for {expression_type}")
 732            try:
 733                return self._parse(parser, raw_tokens, sql)
 734            except ParseError as e:
 735                e.errors[0]["into_expression"] = expression_type
 736                errors.append(e)
 737        raise ParseError(
 738            f"Failed to parse into {expression_types}",
 739            errors=merge_errors(errors),
 740        ) from errors[-1]
 741
 742    def _parse(
 743        self,
 744        parse_method: t.Callable[[Parser], t.Optional[exp.Expression]],
 745        raw_tokens: t.List[Token],
 746        sql: t.Optional[str] = None,
 747    ) -> t.List[t.Optional[exp.Expression]]:
 748        self.reset()
 749        self.sql = sql or ""
 750        total = len(raw_tokens)
 751        chunks: t.List[t.List[Token]] = [[]]
 752
 753        for i, token in enumerate(raw_tokens):
 754            if token.token_type == TokenType.SEMICOLON:
 755                if i < total - 1:
 756                    chunks.append([])
 757            else:
 758                chunks[-1].append(token)
 759
 760        expressions = []
 761
 762        for tokens in chunks:
 763            self._index = -1
 764            self._tokens = tokens
 765            self._advance()
 766
 767            expressions.append(parse_method(self))
 768
 769            if self._index < len(self._tokens):
 770                self.raise_error("Invalid expression / Unexpected token")
 771
 772            self.check_errors()
 773
 774        return expressions
 775
 776    def check_errors(self) -> None:
 777        """
 778        Logs or raises any found errors, depending on the chosen error level setting.
 779        """
 780        if self.error_level == ErrorLevel.WARN:
 781            for error in self.errors:
 782                logger.error(str(error))
 783        elif self.error_level == ErrorLevel.RAISE and self.errors:
 784            raise ParseError(
 785                concat_messages(self.errors, self.max_errors),
 786                errors=merge_errors(self.errors),
 787            )
 788
 789    def raise_error(self, message: str, token: t.Optional[Token] = None) -> None:
 790        """
 791        Appends an error in the list of recorded errors or raises it, depending on the chosen
 792        error level setting.
 793        """
 794        token = token or self._curr or self._prev or Token.string("")
 795        start = self._find_token(token)
 796        end = start + len(token.text)
 797        start_context = self.sql[max(start - self.error_message_context, 0) : start]
 798        highlight = self.sql[start:end]
 799        end_context = self.sql[end : end + self.error_message_context]
 800
 801        error = ParseError.new(
 802            f"{message}. Line {token.line}, Col: {token.col}.\n"
 803            f"  {start_context}\033[4m{highlight}\033[0m{end_context}",
 804            description=message,
 805            line=token.line,
 806            col=token.col,
 807            start_context=start_context,
 808            highlight=highlight,
 809            end_context=end_context,
 810        )
 811
 812        if self.error_level == ErrorLevel.IMMEDIATE:
 813            raise error
 814
 815        self.errors.append(error)
 816
 817    def expression(
 818        self, exp_class: t.Type[exp.Expression], comments: t.Optional[t.List[str]] = None, **kwargs
 819    ) -> exp.Expression:
 820        """
 821        Creates a new, validated Expression.
 822
 823        Args:
 824            exp_class: the expression class to instantiate.
 825            comments: an optional list of comments to attach to the expression.
 826            kwargs: the arguments to set for the expression along with their respective values.
 827
 828        Returns:
 829            The target expression.
 830        """
 831        instance = exp_class(**kwargs)
 832        if self._prev_comments:
 833            instance.comments = self._prev_comments
 834            self._prev_comments = None
 835        if comments:
 836            instance.comments = comments
 837        self.validate_expression(instance)
 838        return instance
 839
 840    def validate_expression(
 841        self, expression: exp.Expression, args: t.Optional[t.List] = None
 842    ) -> None:
 843        """
 844        Validates an already instantiated expression, making sure that all its mandatory arguments
 845        are set.
 846
 847        Args:
 848            expression: the expression to validate.
 849            args: an optional list of items that was used to instantiate the expression, if it's a Func.
 850        """
 851        if self.error_level == ErrorLevel.IGNORE:
 852            return
 853
 854        for error_message in expression.error_messages(args):
 855            self.raise_error(error_message)
 856
 857    def _find_sql(self, start: Token, end: Token) -> str:
 858        return self.sql[self._find_token(start) : self._find_token(end) + len(end.text)]
 859
 860    def _find_token(self, token: Token) -> int:
 861        line = 1
 862        col = 1
 863        index = 0
 864
 865        while line < token.line or col < token.col:
 866            if Tokenizer.WHITE_SPACE.get(self.sql[index]) == TokenType.BREAK:
 867                line += 1
 868                col = 1
 869            else:
 870                col += 1
 871            index += 1
 872
 873        return index
 874
 875    def _advance(self, times: int = 1) -> None:
 876        self._index += times
 877        self._curr = seq_get(self._tokens, self._index)
 878        self._next = seq_get(self._tokens, self._index + 1)
 879        if self._index > 0:
 880            self._prev = self._tokens[self._index - 1]
 881            self._prev_comments = self._prev.comments
 882        else:
 883            self._prev = None
 884            self._prev_comments = None
 885
 886    def _retreat(self, index: int) -> None:
 887        self._advance(index - self._index)
 888
 889    def _parse_command(self) -> exp.Expression:
 890        return self.expression(exp.Command, this=self._prev.text, expression=self._parse_string())
 891
 892    def _parse_statement(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
 893        if self._curr is None:
 894            return None
 895
 896        if self._match_set(self.STATEMENT_PARSERS):
 897            return self.STATEMENT_PARSERS[self._prev.token_type](self)
 898
 899        if self._match_set(Tokenizer.COMMANDS):
 900            return self._parse_command()
 901
 902        expression = self._parse_expression()
 903        expression = self._parse_set_operations(expression) if expression else self._parse_select()
 904
 905        self._parse_query_modifiers(expression)
 906        return expression
 907
 908    def _parse_drop(self, default_kind: t.Optional[str] = None) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
 909        start = self._prev
 910        temporary = self._match(TokenType.TEMPORARY)
 911        materialized = self._match(TokenType.MATERIALIZED)
 912        kind = self._match_set(self.CREATABLES) and self._prev.text
 913        if not kind:
 914            if default_kind:
 915                kind = default_kind
 916            else:
 917                return self._parse_as_command(start)
 918
 919        return self.expression(
 920            exp.Drop,
 921            exists=self._parse_exists(),
 922            this=self._parse_table(schema=True),
 923            kind=kind,
 924            temporary=temporary,
 925            materialized=materialized,
 926            cascade=self._match(TokenType.CASCADE),
 927        )
 928
 929    def _parse_exists(self, not_: bool = False) -> t.Optional[bool]:
 930        return (
 931            self._match(TokenType.IF)
 932            and (not not_ or self._match(TokenType.NOT))
 933            and self._match(TokenType.EXISTS)
 934        )
 935
 936    def _parse_create(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
 937        start = self._prev
 938        replace = self._match_pair(TokenType.OR, TokenType.REPLACE)
 939        set_ = self._match(TokenType.SET)  # Teradata
 940        multiset = self._match_text_seq("MULTISET")  # Teradata
 941        global_temporary = self._match_text_seq("GLOBAL", "TEMPORARY")  # Teradata
 942        volatile = self._match(TokenType.VOLATILE)  # Teradata
 943        temporary = self._match(TokenType.TEMPORARY)
 944        transient = self._match_text_seq("TRANSIENT")
 945        external = self._match_text_seq("EXTERNAL")
 946        unique = self._match(TokenType.UNIQUE)
 947        materialized = self._match(TokenType.MATERIALIZED)
 948
 949        if self._match_pair(TokenType.TABLE, TokenType.FUNCTION, advance=False):
 950            self._match(TokenType.TABLE)
 951
 952        properties = None
 953        create_token = self._match_set(self.CREATABLES) and self._prev
 954
 955        if not create_token:
 956            properties = self._parse_properties()
 957            create_token = self._match_set(self.CREATABLES) and self._prev
 958
 959            if not properties or not create_token:
 960                return self._parse_as_command(start)
 961
 962        exists = self._parse_exists(not_=True)
 963        this = None
 964        expression = None
 965        data = None
 966        statistics = None
 967        no_primary_index = None
 968        indexes = None
 969        no_schema_binding = None
 970        begin = None
 971
 972        if create_token.token_type in (TokenType.FUNCTION, TokenType.PROCEDURE):
 973            this = self._parse_user_defined_function(kind=create_token.token_type)
 974            properties = self._parse_properties()
 975            if self._match(TokenType.ALIAS):
 976                begin = self._match(TokenType.BEGIN)
 977                return_ = self._match_text_seq("RETURN")
 978                expression = self._parse_statement()
 979
 980                if return_:
 981                    expression = self.expression(exp.Return, this=expression)
 982        elif create_token.token_type == TokenType.INDEX:
 983            this = self._parse_index()
 984        elif create_token.token_type in (
 985            TokenType.TABLE,
 986            TokenType.VIEW,
 987            TokenType.SCHEMA,
 988        ):
 989            table_parts = self._parse_table_parts(schema=True)
 990
 991            if self._match(TokenType.COMMA):  # comma-separated properties before schema definition
 992                properties = self._parse_properties(before=True)
 993
 994            this = self._parse_schema(this=table_parts)
 995
 996            if not properties:  # properties after schema definition
 997                properties = self._parse_properties()
 998
 999            self._match(TokenType.ALIAS)
1000            expression = self._parse_ddl_select()
1001
1002            if create_token.token_type == TokenType.TABLE:
1003                if self._match_text_seq("WITH", "DATA"):
1004                    data = True
1005                elif self._match_text_seq("WITH", "NO", "DATA"):
1006                    data = False
1007
1008                if self._match_text_seq("AND", "STATISTICS"):
1009                    statistics = True
1010                elif self._match_text_seq("AND", "NO", "STATISTICS"):
1011                    statistics = False
1012
1013                no_primary_index = self._match_text_seq("NO", "PRIMARY", "INDEX")
1014
1015                indexes = []
1016                while True:
1017                    index = self._parse_create_table_index()
1018
1019                    # post index PARTITION BY property
1020                    if self._match(TokenType.PARTITION_BY, advance=False):
1021                        if properties:
1022                            properties.expressions.append(self._parse_property())
1023                        else:
1024                            properties = self._parse_properties()
1025
1026                    if not index:
1027                        break
1028                    else:
1029                        indexes.append(index)
1030            elif create_token.token_type == TokenType.VIEW:
1031                if self._match_text_seq("WITH", "NO", "SCHEMA", "BINDING"):
1032                    no_schema_binding = True
1033
1034        return self.expression(
1035            exp.Create,
1036            this=this,
1037            kind=create_token.text,
1038            expression=expression,
1039            set=set_,
1040            multiset=multiset,
1041            global_temporary=global_temporary,
1042            volatile=volatile,
1043            exists=exists,
1044            properties=properties,
1045            temporary=temporary,
1046            transient=transient,
1047            external=external,
1048            replace=replace,
1049            unique=unique,
1050            materialized=materialized,
1051            data=data,
1052            statistics=statistics,
1053            no_primary_index=no_primary_index,
1054            indexes=indexes,
1055            no_schema_binding=no_schema_binding,
1056            begin=begin,
1057        )
1058
1059    def _parse_property_before(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1060        self._match(TokenType.COMMA)
1061
1062        # parsers look to _prev for no/dual/default, so need to consume first
1063        self._match_text_seq("NO")
1064        self._match_text_seq("DUAL")
1065        self._match_text_seq("DEFAULT")
1066
1067        if self.PROPERTY_PARSERS.get(self._curr.text.upper()):
1068            return self.PROPERTY_PARSERS[self._curr.text.upper()](self)
1069
1070        return None
1071
1072    def _parse_property(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1073        if self._match_texts(self.PROPERTY_PARSERS):
1074            return self.PROPERTY_PARSERS[self._prev.text.upper()](self)
1075
1076        if self._match_pair(TokenType.DEFAULT, TokenType.CHARACTER_SET):
1077            return self._parse_character_set(True)
1078
1079        if self._match_pair(TokenType.COMPOUND, TokenType.SORTKEY):
1080            return self._parse_sortkey(compound=True)
1081
1082        if self._match_text_seq("SQL", "SECURITY"):
1083            return self.expression(exp.SqlSecurityProperty, definer=self._match_text_seq("DEFINER"))
1084
1085        assignment = self._match_pair(
1086            TokenType.VAR, TokenType.EQ, advance=False
1087        ) or self._match_pair(TokenType.STRING, TokenType.EQ, advance=False)
1088
1089        if assignment:
1090            key = self._parse_var_or_string()
1091            self._match(TokenType.EQ)
1092            return self.expression(exp.Property, this=key, value=self._parse_column())
1093
1094        return None
1095
1096    def _parse_property_assignment(self, exp_class: t.Type[exp.Expression]) -> exp.Expression:
1097        self._match(TokenType.EQ)
1098        self._match(TokenType.ALIAS)
1099        return self.expression(
1100            exp_class,
1101            this=self._parse_var_or_string() or self._parse_number() or self._parse_id_var(),
1102        )
1103
1104    def _parse_properties(self, before=None) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1105        properties = []
1106
1107        while True:
1108            if before:
1109                identified_property = self._parse_property_before()
1110            else:
1111                identified_property = self._parse_property()
1112
1113            if not identified_property:
1114                break
1115            for p in ensure_collection(identified_property):
1116                properties.append(p)
1117
1118        if properties:
1119            return self.expression(exp.Properties, expressions=properties)
1120
1121        return None
1122
1123    def _parse_fallback(self, no=False) -> exp.Expression:
1124        self._match_text_seq("FALLBACK")
1125        return self.expression(
1126            exp.FallbackProperty, no=no, protection=self._match_text_seq("PROTECTION")
1127        )

1129    def _parse_with_property(
1130        self,
1131    ) -> t.Union[t.Optional[exp.Expression], t.List[t.Optional[exp.Expression]]]:
1132        if self._match(TokenType.L_PAREN, advance=False):
1133            return self._parse_wrapped_csv(self._parse_property)
1134
1135        if not self._next:
1136            return None
1137
1138        if self._next.text.upper() == "JOURNAL":
1139            return self._parse_withjournaltable()
1140
1141        return self._parse_withisolatedloading()
1142
1143    # https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/create-view.html
1144    def _parse_definer(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1145        self._match(TokenType.EQ)
1146
1147        user = self._parse_id_var()
1148        self._match(TokenType.PARAMETER)
1149        host = self._parse_id_var() or (self._match(TokenType.MOD) and self._prev.text)
1150
1151        if not user or not host:
1152            return None
1153
1154        return exp.DefinerProperty(this=f"{user}@{host}")
1155
1156    def _parse_withjournaltable(self) -> exp.Expression:
1157        self._match_text_seq("WITH", "JOURNAL", "TABLE")
1158        self._match(TokenType.EQ)
1159        return self.expression(exp.WithJournalTableProperty, this=self._parse_table_parts())

1161    def _parse_log(self, no=False) -> exp.Expression:
1162        self._match_text_seq("LOG")
1163        return self.expression(exp.LogProperty, no=no)
1164
1165    def _parse_journal(self, no=False, dual=False) -> exp.Expression:
1166        before = self._match_text_seq("BEFORE")
1167        self._match_text_seq("JOURNAL")
1168        return self.expression(exp.JournalProperty, no=no, dual=dual, before=before)
1169
1170    def _parse_afterjournal(self, no=False, dual=False, local=None) -> exp.Expression:
1171        self._match_text_seq("NOT")
1172        self._match_text_seq("LOCAL")
1173        self._match_text_seq("AFTER", "JOURNAL")
1174        return self.expression(exp.AfterJournalProperty, no=no, dual=dual, local=local)

1176    def _parse_checksum(self) -> exp.Expression:
1177        self._match_text_seq("CHECKSUM")
1178        self._match(TokenType.EQ)
1179
1180        on = None
1181        if self._match(TokenType.ON):
1182            on = True
1183        elif self._match_text_seq("OFF"):
1184            on = False
1185        default = self._match(TokenType.DEFAULT)
1186
1187        return self.expression(
1188            exp.ChecksumProperty,

1342    def _parse_insert(self) -> exp.Expression:
1343        overwrite = self._match(TokenType.OVERWRITE)
1344        local = self._match(TokenType.LOCAL)

1346        this: t.Optional[exp.Expression]

1354            )
1355        else:

1361            exp.Insert,

1374    def _parse_row_format(self, match_row: bool = False) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1375        if match_row and not self._match_pair(TokenType.ROW, TokenType.FORMAT):
1376            return None
1377
1378        if self._match_text_seq("SERDE"):
1379            return self.expression(exp.RowFormatSerdeProperty, this=self._parse_string())
1380
1381        self._match_text_seq("DELIMITED")
1382
1383        kwargs = {}
1384
1385        if self._match_text_seq("FIELDS", "TERMINATED", "BY"):
1386            kwargs["fields"] = self._parse_string()
1387            if self._match_text_seq("ESCAPED", "BY"):
1388                kwargs["escaped"] = self._parse_string()
1389        if self._match_text_seq("COLLECTION", "ITEMS", "TERMINATED", "BY"):
1390            kwargs["collection_items"] = self._parse_string()
1391        if self._match_text_seq("MAP", "KEYS", "TERMINATED", "BY"):
1392            kwargs["map_keys"] = self._parse_string()
1393        if self._match_text_seq("LINES", "TERMINATED", "BY"):
1394            kwargs["lines"] = self._parse_string()
1395        if self._match_text_seq("NULL", "DEFINED", "AS"):
1396            kwargs["null"] = self._parse_string()
1397
1398        return self.expression(exp.RowFormatDelimitedProperty, **kwargs)  # type: ignore

1480    def _parse_value(self) -> exp.Expression:
1481        if self._match(TokenType.L_PAREN):
1482            expressions = self._parse_csv(self._parse_conjunction)
1483            self._match_r_paren()
1484            return self.expression(exp.Tuple, expressions=expressions)
1485
1486        # In presto we can have VALUES 1, 2 which results in 1 column & 2 rows.
1487        # Source: https://prestodb.io/docs/current/sql/values.html
1488        return self.expression(exp.Tuple, expressions=[self._parse_conjunction()])

1490    def _parse_select(
1491        self, nested: bool = False, table: bool = False, parse_subquery_alias: bool = True
1492    ) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1493        cte = self._parse_with()
1494        if cte:
1495            this = self._parse_statement()
1496
1497            if not this:
1498                self.raise_error("Failed to parse any statement following CTE")
1499                return cte
1500
1501            if "with" in this.arg_types:
1502                this.set("with", cte)
1503            else:
1504                self.raise_error(f"{this.key} does not support CTE")
1505                this = cte
1506        elif self._match(TokenType.SELECT):
1507            comments = self._prev_comments
1508
1509            hint = self._parse_hint()
1510            all_ = self._match(TokenType.ALL)
1511            distinct = self._match(TokenType.DISTINCT)
1512
1513            if distinct:
1514                distinct = self.expression(
1515                    exp.Distinct,
1516                    on=self._parse_value() if self._match(TokenType.ON) else None,
1517                )
1518
1519            if all_ and distinct:
1520                self.raise_error("Cannot specify both ALL and DISTINCT after SELECT")
1521
1522            limit = self._parse_limit(top=True)
1523            expressions = self._parse_csv(self._parse_expression)
1524
1525            this = self.expression(
1526                exp.Select,
1527                hint=hint,
1528                distinct=distinct,
1529                expressions=expressions,
1530                limit=limit,
1531            )
1532            this.comments = comments
1533
1534            into = self._parse_into()
1535            if into:
1536                this.set("into", into)
1537
1538            from_ = self._parse_from()
1539            if from_:
1540                this.set("from", from_)
1541
1542            self._parse_query_modifiers(this)
1543        elif (table or nested) and self._match(TokenType.L_PAREN):
1544            this = self._parse_table() if table else self._parse_select(nested=True)
1545            self._parse_query_modifiers(this)
1546            this = self._parse_set_operations(this)
1547            self._match_r_paren()
1548
1549            # early return so that subquery unions aren't parsed again
1550            # SELECT * FROM (SELECT 1) UNION ALL SELECT 1
1551            # Union ALL should be a property of the top select node, not the subquery
1552            return self._parse_subquery(this, parse_alias=parse_subquery_alias)
1553        elif self._match(TokenType.VALUES):
1554            this = self.expression(
1555                exp.Values,
1556                expressions=self._parse_csv(self._parse_value),
1557                alias=self._parse_table_alias(),
1558            )
1559        else:
1560            this = None
1561
1562        return self._parse_set_operations(this)
1563
1564    def _parse_with(self, skip_with_token: bool = False) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1565        if not skip_with_token and not self._match(TokenType.WITH):
1566            return None
1567
1568        recursive = self._match(TokenType.RECURSIVE)
1569
1570        expressions = []
1571        while True:
1572            expressions.append(self._parse_cte())
1573
1574            if not self._match(TokenType.COMMA) and not self._match(TokenType.WITH):
1575                break
1576            else:
1577                self._match(TokenType.WITH)
1578
1579        return self.expression(exp.With, expressions=expressions, recursive=recursive)
1580
1581    def _parse_cte(self) -> exp.Expression:
1582        alias = self._parse_table_alias()
1583        if not alias or not alias.this:
1584            self.raise_error("Expected CTE to have alias")
1585
1586        self._match(TokenType.ALIAS)
1587
1588        return self.expression(
1589            exp.CTE,
1590            this=self._parse_wrapped(self._parse_statement),
1591            alias=alias,
1592        )
1593
1594    def _parse_table_alias(
1595        self, alias_tokens: t.Optional[t.Collection[TokenType]] = None
1596    ) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1597        any_token = self._match(TokenType.ALIAS)
1598        alias = self._parse_id_var(
1599            any_token=any_token, tokens=alias_tokens or self.TABLE_ALIAS_TOKENS
1600        )
1601        index = self._index
1602
1603        if self._match(TokenType.L_PAREN):
1604            columns = self._parse_csv(lambda: self._parse_column_def(self._parse_id_var()))
1605            self._match_r_paren() if columns else self._retreat(index)
1606        else:
1607            columns = None
1608
1609        if not alias and not columns:
1610            return None
1611
1612        return self.expression(exp.TableAlias, this=alias, columns=columns)
1613
1614    def _parse_subquery(
1615        self, this: t.Optional[exp.Expression], parse_alias: bool = True
1616    ) -> exp.Expression:
1617        return self.expression(
1618            exp.Subquery,
1619            this=this,
1620            pivots=self._parse_pivots(),
1621            alias=self._parse_table_alias() if parse_alias else None,
1622        )

1624    def _parse_query_modifiers(self, this: t.Optional[exp.Expression]) -> None:
1625        if not isinstance(this, self.MODIFIABLES):
1626            return
1627
1628        table = isinstance(this, exp.Table)
1629
1630        while True:
1631            lateral = self._parse_lateral()
1632            join = self._parse_join()
1633            comma = None if table else self._match(TokenType.COMMA)
1634            if lateral:
1635                this.append("laterals", lateral)
1636            if join:
1637                this.append("joins", join)
1638            if comma:
1639                this.args["from"].append("expressions", self._parse_table())
1640            if not (lateral or join or comma):
1641                break
1642
1643        for key, parser in self.QUERY_MODIFIER_PARSERS.items():
1644            expression = parser(self)
1645
1646            if expression:
1647                this.set(key, expression)
1648
1649    def _parse_hint(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1650        if self._match(TokenType.HINT):
1651            hints = self._parse_csv(self._parse_function)
1652            if not self._match_pair(TokenType.STAR, TokenType.SLASH):
1653                self.raise_error("Expected */ after HINT")
1654            return self.expression(exp.Hint, expressions=hints)
1655
1656        return None

1658    def _parse_into(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:

1660            return None
1661
1662        temp = self._match(TokenType.TEMPORARY)
1663        unlogged = self._match(TokenType.UNLOGGED)
1664        self._match(TokenType.TABLE)
1665
1666        return self.expression(
1667            exp.Into, this=self._parse_table(schema=True), temporary=temp, unlogged=unlogged
1668        )
1669
1670    def _parse_from(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1671        if not self._match(TokenType.FROM):
1672            return None
1673
1674        return self.expression(
1675            exp.From, comments=self._prev_comments, expressions=self._parse_csv(self._parse_table)
1676        )

1678    def _parse_match_recognize(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1679        if not self._match(TokenType.MATCH_RECOGNIZE):
1680            return None
1681        self._match_l_paren()
1682
1683        partition = self._parse_partition_by()
1684        order = self._parse_order()
1685        measures = (
1686            self._parse_alias(self._parse_conjunction())
1687            if self._match_text_seq("MEASURES")
1688            else None
1689        )
1690
1691        if self._match_text_seq("ONE", "ROW", "PER", "MATCH"):
1692            rows = exp.Var(this="ONE ROW PER MATCH")
1693        elif self._match_text_seq("ALL", "ROWS", "PER", "MATCH"):
1694            text = "ALL ROWS PER MATCH"
1695            if self._match_text_seq("SHOW", "EMPTY", "MATCHES"):
1696                text += f" SHOW EMPTY MATCHES"
1697            elif self._match_text_seq("OMIT", "EMPTY", "MATCHES"):
1698                text += f" OMIT EMPTY MATCHES"
1699            elif self._match_text_seq("WITH", "UNMATCHED", "ROWS"):
1700                text += f" WITH UNMATCHED ROWS"
1701            rows = exp.Var(this=text)
1702        else:
1703            rows = None
1704
1705        if self._match_text_seq("AFTER", "MATCH", "SKIP"):
1706            text = "AFTER MATCH SKIP"
1707            if self._match_text_seq("PAST", "LAST", "ROW"):
1708                text += f" PAST LAST ROW"
1709            elif self._match_text_seq("TO", "NEXT", "ROW"):
1710                text += f" TO NEXT ROW"
1711            elif self._match_text_seq("TO", "FIRST"):
1712                text += f" TO FIRST {self._advance_any().text}"  # type: ignore
1713            elif self._match_text_seq("TO", "LAST"):
1714                text += f" TO LAST {self._advance_any().text}"  # type: ignore
1715            after = exp.Var(this=text)
1716        else:
1717            after = None
1718
1719        if self._match_text_seq("PATTERN"):
1720            self._match_l_paren()
1721
1722            if not self._curr:
1723                self.raise_error("Expecting )", self._curr)
1724
1725            paren = 1
1726            start = self._curr
1727
1728            while self._curr and paren > 0:
1729                if self._curr.token_type == TokenType.L_PAREN:
1730                    paren += 1
1731                if self._curr.token_type == TokenType.R_PAREN:
1732                    paren -= 1
1733                end = self._prev
1734                self._advance()
1735            if paren > 0:
1736                self.raise_error("Expecting )", self._curr)
1737            pattern = exp.Var(this=self._find_sql(start, end))
1738        else:
1739            pattern = None
1740
1741        define = (
1742            self._parse_alias(self._parse_conjunction()) if self._match_text_seq("DEFINE") else None
1743        )
1744        self._match_r_paren()
1745
1746        return self.expression(
1747            exp.MatchRecognize,
1748            partition_by=partition,
1749            order=order,
1750            measures=measures,
1751            rows=rows,
1752            after=after,
1753            pattern=pattern,
1754            define=define,
1755        )
1756
1757    def _parse_lateral(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1758        outer_apply = self._match_pair(TokenType.OUTER, TokenType.APPLY)
1759        cross_apply = self._match_pair(TokenType.CROSS, TokenType.APPLY)
1760
1761        if outer_apply or cross_apply:
1762            this = self._parse_select(table=True)
1763            view = None
1764            outer = not cross_apply
1765        elif self._match(TokenType.LATERAL):
1766            this = self._parse_select(table=True)
1767            view = self._match(TokenType.VIEW)
1768            outer = self._match(TokenType.OUTER)
1769        else:
1770            return None
1771
1772        if not this:
1773            this = self._parse_function() or self._parse_id_var(any_token=False)
1774            while self._match(TokenType.DOT):
1775                this = exp.Dot(
1776                    this=this,
1777                    expression=self._parse_function() or self._parse_id_var(any_token=False),
1778                )
1779
1780        table_alias: t.Optional[exp.Expression]
1781
1782        if view:
1783            table = self._parse_id_var(any_token=False)
1784            columns = self._parse_csv(self._parse_id_var) if self._match(TokenType.ALIAS) else []
1785            table_alias = self.expression(exp.TableAlias, this=table, columns=columns)
1786        else:
1787            table_alias = self._parse_table_alias()
1788
1789        expression = self.expression(
1790            exp.Lateral,
1791            this=this,
1792            view=view,
1793            outer=outer,
1794            alias=table_alias,
1795        )
1796
1797        if outer_apply or cross_apply:
1798            return self.expression(exp.Join, this=expression, side=None if cross_apply else "LEFT")
1799
1800        return expression
1801
1802    def _parse_join_side_and_kind(
1803        self,

1866    def _parse_table_parts(self, schema: bool = False) -> exp.Expression:
1867        catalog = None
1868        db = None
1869        table = (not schema and self._parse_function()) or self._parse_id_var(any_token=False)
1870
1871        while self._match(TokenType.DOT):
1872            if catalog:
1873                # This allows nesting the table in arbitrarily many dot expressions if needed
1874                table = self.expression(exp.Dot, this=table, expression=self._parse_id_var())
1875            else:
1876                catalog = db
1877                db = table
1878                table = self._parse_id_var()
1879
1880        if not table:
1881            self.raise_error(f"Expected table name but got {self._curr}")
1882
1883        return self.expression(
1884            exp.Table, this=table, db=db, catalog=catalog, pivots=self._parse_pivots()
1885        )

1887    def _parse_table(
1888        self, schema: bool = False, alias_tokens: t.Optional[t.Collection[TokenType]] = None
1889    ) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
1890        lateral = self._parse_lateral()
1891
1892        if lateral:
1893            return lateral
1894
1895        unnest = self._parse_unnest()
1896
1897        if unnest:
1898            return unnest
1899
1900        values = self._parse_derived_table_values()
1901
1902        if values:
1903            return values
1904
1905        subquery = self._parse_select(table=True)
1906
1907        if subquery:
1908            return subquery
1909
1910        this = self._parse_table_parts(schema=schema)
1911
1912        if schema:
1913            return self._parse_schema(this=this)
1914
1915        if self.alias_post_tablesample:
1916            table_sample = self._parse_table_sample()
1917
1918        alias = self._parse_table_alias(alias_tokens=alias_tokens or self.TABLE_ALIAS_TOKENS)
1919
1920        if alias:
1921            this.set("alias", alias)
1922
1923        if self._match_pair(TokenType.WITH, TokenType.L_PAREN):
1924            this.set(
1925                "hints",
1926                self._parse_csv(lambda: self._parse_function() or self._parse_var(any_token=True)),
1927            )
1928            self._match_r_paren()
1929
1930        if not self.alias_post_tablesample:
1931            table_sample = self._parse_table_sample()
1932
1933        if table_sample:
1934            table_sample.set("this", this)
1935            this = table_sample
1936
1937        return this

1939    def _parse_unnest(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:

2417                value = exp.DataType(this=exp.DataType.Type.TIMESTAMPTZ, expressions=expressions)

2419                self._match(TokenType.WITH_LOCAL_TIME_ZONE) or type_token == TokenType.TIMESTAMPLTZ
2420            ):
2421                value = exp.DataType(this=exp.DataType.Type.TIMESTAMPLTZ, expressions=expressions)
2422            elif self._match(TokenType.WITHOUT_TIME_ZONE):
2423                if type_token == TokenType.TIME:
2424                    value = exp.DataType(this=exp.DataType.Type.TIME, expressions=expressions)
2425                else:
2426                    value = exp.DataType(this=exp.DataType.Type.TIMESTAMP, expressions=expressions)
2427
2428            maybe_func = maybe_func and value is None
2429
2430            if value is None:
2431                value = exp.DataType(this=exp.DataType.Type.TIMESTAMP, expressions=expressions)
2432        elif type_token == TokenType.INTERVAL:
2433            value = self.expression(exp.Interval, unit=self._parse_var())
2434
2435        if maybe_func and check_func:
2436            index2 = self._index
2437            peek = self._parse_string()
2438
2439            if not peek:
2440                self._retreat(index)
2441                return None
2442
2443            self._retreat(index2)
2444
2445        if value:
2446            return value
2447
2448        return exp.DataType(
2449            this=exp.DataType.Type[type_token.value.upper()],
2450            expressions=expressions,
2451            nested=nested,
2452            values=values,
2453        )

2472    def _parse_column(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
2473        this = self._parse_field()
2474        if isinstance(this, exp.Identifier):
2475            this = self.expression(exp.Column, this=this)
2476        elif not this:
2477            return self._parse_bracket(this)
2478        this = self._parse_bracket(this)
2479
2480        while self._match_set(self.COLUMN_OPERATORS):
2481            op_token = self._prev.token_type
2482            op = self.COLUMN_OPERATORS.get(op_token)
2483
2484            if op_token == TokenType.DCOLON:
2485                field = self._parse_types()
2486                if not field:
2487                    self.raise_error("Expected type")
2488            elif op:
2489                self._advance()
2490                value = self._prev.text
2491                field = (
2492                    exp.Literal.number(value)
2493                    if self._prev.token_type == TokenType.NUMBER
2494                    else exp.Literal.string(value)
2495                )
2496            else:
2497                field = self._parse_star() or self._parse_function() or self._parse_id_var()
2498
2499            if isinstance(field, exp.Func):
2500                # bigquery allows function calls like x.y.count(...)
2501                # SAFE.SUBSTR(...)
2502                # https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/standard-sql/functions-reference#function_call_rules
2503                this = self._replace_columns_with_dots(this)
2504
2505            if op:
2506                this = op(self, this, field)
2507            elif isinstance(this, exp.Column) and not this.table:
2508                this = self.expression(exp.Column, this=field, table=this.this)
2509            else:
2510                this = self.expression(exp.Dot, this=this, expression=field)
2511            this = self._parse_bracket(this)
2512
2513        return this

2515    def _parse_primary(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
2516        if self._match_set(self.PRIMARY_PARSERS):
2517            token_type = self._prev.token_type
2518            primary = self.PRIMARY_PARSERS[token_type](self, self._prev)
2519
2520            if token_type == TokenType.STRING:
2521                expressions = [primary]
2522                while self._match(TokenType.STRING):
2523                    expressions.append(exp.Literal.string(self._prev.text))
2524                if len(expressions) > 1:
2525                    return self.expression(exp.Concat, expressions=expressions)
2526            return primary
2527
2528        if self._match_pair(TokenType.DOT, TokenType.NUMBER):
2529            return exp.Literal.number(f"0.{self._prev.text}")
2530
2531        if self._match(TokenType.L_PAREN):
2532            comments = self._prev_comments
2533            query = self._parse_select()
2534
2535            if query:
2536                expressions = [query]
2537            else:
2538                expressions = self._parse_csv(
2539                    lambda: self._parse_alias(self._parse_conjunction(), explicit=True)
2540                )
2541
2542            this = seq_get(expressions, 0)
2543            self._parse_query_modifiers(this)
2544            self._match_r_paren()
2545
2546            if isinstance(this, exp.Subqueryable):
2547                this = self._parse_set_operations(
2548                    self._parse_subquery(this=this, parse_alias=False)
2549                )
2550            elif len(expressions) > 1:
2551                this = self.expression(exp.Tuple, expressions=expressions)
2552            else:
2553                this = self.expression(exp.Paren, this=this)
2554
2555            if this and comments:
2556                this.comments = comments
2557
2558            return this
2559
2560        return None

2565    def _parse_function(
2566        self, functions: t.Optional[t.Dict[str, t.Callable]] = None
2567    ) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
2568        if not self._curr:
2569            return None
2570
2571        token_type = self._curr.token_type
2572
2573        if self._match_set(self.NO_PAREN_FUNCTION_PARSERS):
2574            return self.NO_PAREN_FUNCTION_PARSERS[token_type](self)
2575
2576        if not self._next or self._next.token_type != TokenType.L_PAREN:
2577            if token_type in self.NO_PAREN_FUNCTIONS:
2578                self._advance()
2579                return self.expression(self.NO_PAREN_FUNCTIONS[token_type])
2580
2581            return None
2582
2583        if token_type not in self.FUNC_TOKENS:
2584            return None
2585
2586        this = self._curr.text
2587        upper = this.upper()
2588        self._advance(2)
2589
2590        parser = self.FUNCTION_PARSERS.get(upper)
2591
2592        if parser:
2593            this = parser(self)
2594        else:
2595            subquery_predicate = self.SUBQUERY_PREDICATES.get(token_type)
2596
2597            if subquery_predicate and self._curr.token_type in (TokenType.SELECT, TokenType.WITH):
2598                this = self.expression(subquery_predicate, this=self._parse_select())
2599                self._match_r_paren()
2600                return this
2601
2602            if functions is None:
2603                functions = self.FUNCTIONS
2604
2605            function = functions.get(upper)
2606            args = self._parse_csv(self._parse_lambda)
2607
2608            if function:
2609                # Clickhouse supports function calls like foo(x, y)(z), so for these we need to also parse the
2610                # second parameter list (i.e. "(z)") and the corresponding function will receive both arg lists.
2611                if count_params(function) == 2:
2612                    params = None
2613                    if self._match_pair(TokenType.R_PAREN, TokenType.L_PAREN):
2614                        params = self._parse_csv(self._parse_lambda)
2615
2616                    this = function(args, params)
2617                else:
2618                    this = function(args)
2619
2620                self.validate_expression(this, args)
2621            else:
2622                this = self.expression(exp.Anonymous, this=this, expressions=args)
2623
2624        self._match_r_paren(this)
2625        return self._parse_window(this)

2733    def _parse_column_constraint(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
2734        this = self._parse_references()

2736        if this:
2737            return this
2738
2739        if self._match(TokenType.CONSTRAINT):
2740            this = self._parse_id_var()
2741
2742        kind: exp.Expression
2743
2744        if self._match(TokenType.AUTO_INCREMENT):

2753        elif self._match(TokenType.DEFAULT):

2755        elif self._match_pair(TokenType.NOT, TokenType.NULL):

2771            else:

2778                    kind.set("start", self._parse_bitwise())
2779                if self._match_text_seq("INCREMENT", "BY"):

2811    def _parse_key_constraint_options(self) -> t.List[str]:
2812        options = []
2813        while True:
2814            if not self._curr:
2815                break
2816
2817            if self._match(TokenType.ON):
2818                action = None
2819                on = self._advance_any() and self._prev.text
2820
2821                if self._match(TokenType.NO_ACTION):
2822                    action = "NO ACTION"
2823                elif self._match(TokenType.CASCADE):
2824                    action = "CASCADE"
2825                elif self._match_pair(TokenType.SET, TokenType.NULL):
2826                    action = "SET NULL"
2827                elif self._match_pair(TokenType.SET, TokenType.DEFAULT):
2828                    action = "SET DEFAULT"
2829                else:
2830                    self.raise_error("Invalid key constraint")
2831
2832                options.append(f"ON {on} {action}")
2833            elif self._match_text_seq("NOT", "ENFORCED"):
2834                options.append("NOT ENFORCED")
2835            elif self._match_text_seq("DEFERRABLE"):
2836                options.append("DEFERRABLE")
2837            elif self._match_text_seq("INITIALLY", "DEFERRED"):
2838                options.append("INITIALLY DEFERRED")
2839            elif self._match_text_seq("NORELY"):
2840                options.append("NORELY")
2841            elif self._match_text_seq("MATCH", "FULL"):
2842                options.append("MATCH FULL")
2843            else:
2844                break
2845
2846        return options

2892    def _parse_bracket(self, this: t.Optional[exp.Expression]) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
2893        if not self._match_set((TokenType.L_BRACKET, TokenType.L_BRACE)):
2894            return this
2895
2896        bracket_kind = self._prev.token_type
2897        expressions: t.List[t.Optional[exp.Expression]]
2898
2899        if self._match(TokenType.COLON):
2900            expressions = [self.expression(exp.Slice, expression=self._parse_conjunction())]
2901        else:
2902            expressions = self._parse_csv(lambda: self._parse_slice(self._parse_conjunction()))
2903
2904        # https://duckdb.org/docs/sql/data_types/struct.html#creating-structs
2905        if bracket_kind == TokenType.L_BRACE:
2906            this = self.expression(exp.Struct, expressions=expressions)
2907        elif not this or this.name.upper() == "ARRAY":
2908            this = self.expression(exp.Array, expressions=expressions)
2909        else:
2910            expressions = apply_index_offset(expressions, -self.index_offset)
2911            this = self.expression(exp.Bracket, this=this, expressions=expressions)
2912
2913        if not self._match(TokenType.R_BRACKET) and bracket_kind == TokenType.L_BRACKET:
2914            self.raise_error("Expected ]")
2915        elif not self._match(TokenType.R_BRACE) and bracket_kind == TokenType.L_BRACE:
2916            self.raise_error("Expected }")
2917
2918        this.comments = self._prev_comments
2919        return self._parse_bracket(this)

3013            self.validate_expression(this, args)
3014            return this
3015
3016        self._match_l_paren()  # The corresponding match_r_paren will be called in parse_function (caller)
3017        order = self._parse_order(this=expression)
3018        return self.expression(exp.GroupConcat, this=order, separator=seq_get(args, 1))

3108    def _parse_window(
3109        self, this: t.Optional[exp.Expression], alias: bool = False
3110    ) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:
3111        if self._match(TokenType.FILTER):
3112            where = self._parse_wrapped(self._parse_where)
3113            this = self.expression(exp.Filter, this=this, expression=where)
3114
3115        # T-SQL allows the OVER (...) syntax after WITHIN GROUP.
3116        # https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/t-sql/functions/percentile-disc-transact-sql?view=sql-server-ver16
3117        if self._match(TokenType.WITHIN_GROUP):
3118            order = self._parse_wrapped(self._parse_order)
3119            this = self.expression(exp.WithinGroup, this=this, expression=order)
3120
3121        # SQL spec defines an optional [ { IGNORE | RESPECT } NULLS ] OVER
3122        # Some dialects choose to implement and some do not.
3123        # https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/window-function-descriptions.html
3124
3125        # There is some code above in _parse_lambda that handles
3126        #   SELECT FIRST_VALUE(TABLE.COLUMN IGNORE|RESPECT NULLS) OVER ...
3127
3128        # The below changes handle
3129        #   SELECT FIRST_VALUE(TABLE.COLUMN) IGNORE|RESPECT NULLS OVER ...
3130
3131        # Oracle allows both formats
3132        #   (https://docs.oracle.com/en/database/oracle/oracle-database/19/sqlrf/img_text/first_value.html)
3133        #   and Snowflake chose to do the same for familiarity
3134        #   https://docs.snowflake.com/en/sql-reference/functions/first_value.html#usage-notes
3135        if self._match(TokenType.IGNORE_NULLS):
3136            this = self.expression(exp.IgnoreNulls, this=this)
3137        elif self._match(TokenType.RESPECT_NULLS):
3138            this = self.expression(exp.RespectNulls, this=this)
3139
3140        # bigquery select from window x AS (partition by ...)
3141        if alias:
3142            self._match(TokenType.ALIAS)
3143        elif not self._match(TokenType.OVER):
3144            return this
3145
3146        if not self._match(TokenType.L_PAREN):
3147            return self.expression(exp.Window, this=this, alias=self._parse_id_var(False))
3148
3149        window_alias = self._parse_id_var(any_token=False, tokens=self.WINDOW_ALIAS_TOKENS)
3150        partition = self._parse_partition_by()
3151        order = self._parse_order()
3152        kind = self._match_set((TokenType.ROWS, TokenType.RANGE)) and self._prev.text
3153
3154        if kind:
3155            self._match(TokenType.BETWEEN)
3156            start = self._parse_window_spec()
3157            self._match(TokenType.AND)
3158            end = self._parse_window_spec()
3159
3160            spec = self.expression(
3161                exp.WindowSpec,
3162                kind=kind,
3163                start=start["value"],
3164                start_side=start["side"],
3165                end=end["value"],
3166                end_side=end["side"],
3167            )
3168        else:
3169            spec = None
3170
3171        self._match_r_paren()
3172
3173        return self.expression(
3174            exp.Window,
3175            this=this,
3176            partition_by=partition,
3177            order=order,
3178            spec=spec,
3179            alias=window_alias,
3180        )

3444    def _parse_alter(self) -> t.Optional[exp.Expression]:

3570    def _find_parser(
3571        self, parsers: t.Dict[str, t.Callable], trie: t.Dict
3572    ) -> t.Optional[t.Callable]:
3573        index = self._index
3574        this = []
3575        while True:
3576            # The current token might be multiple words
3577            curr = self._curr.text.upper()
3578            key = curr.split(" ")
3579            this.append(curr)
3580            self._advance()
3581            result, trie = in_trie(trie, key)
3582            if result == 0:
3583                break
3584            if result == 2:
3585                subparser = parsers[" ".join(this)]
3586                return subparser
3587        self._retreat(index)
3588        return None

3590    def _match(self, token_type, advance=True):
3591        if not self._curr:
3592            return None
3593
3594        if self._curr.token_type == token_type:
3595            if advance:
3596                self._advance()
3597            return True
3598
3599        return None
3600
3601    def _match_set(self, types):
3602        if not self._curr:
3603            return None
3604
3605        if self._curr.token_type in types:
3606            self._advance()
3607            return True
3608
3609        return None
3610
3611    def _match_pair(self, token_type_a, token_type_b, advance=True):
3612        if not self._curr or not self._next:
3613            return None
3614
3615        if self._curr.token_type == token_type_a and self._next.token_type == token_type_b:
3616            if advance:
3617                self._advance(2)
3618            return True
3619
3620        return None

3622    def _match_l_paren(self, expression=None):
3623        if not self._match(TokenType.L_PAREN):
3624            self.raise_error("Expecting (")
3625        if expression and self._prev_comments:
3626            expression.comments = self._prev_comments
3627
3628    def _match_r_paren(self, expression=None):
3629        if not self._match(TokenType.R_PAREN):
3630            self.raise_error("Expecting )")
3631        if expression and self._prev_comments:
3632            expression.comments = self._prev_comments

3634    def _match_texts(self, texts):
3635        if self._curr and self._curr.text.upper() in texts:
3636            self._advance()
3637            return True
3638        return False
