3640    def _match_text_seq(self, *texts, advance=True):
3641        index = self._index
3642        for text in texts:
3643            if self._curr and self._curr.text.upper() == text:
3644                self._advance()
3645            else:
3646                self._retreat(index)
3647                return False
3648
3649        if not advance:
3650            self._retreat(index)
3651
3652        return True

3654    def _replace_columns_with_dots(self, this):
3655        if isinstance(this, exp.Dot):
3656            exp.replace_children(this, self._replace_columns_with_dots)
3657        elif isinstance(this, exp.Column):
3658            exp.replace_children(this, self._replace_columns_with_dots)
3659            table = this.args.get("table")
3660            this = (
3661                self.expression(exp.Dot, this=table, expression=this.this)
3662                if table
3663                else self.expression(exp.Var, this=this.name)
3664            )
3665        elif isinstance(this, exp.Identifier):
3666            this = self.expression(exp.Var, this=this.name)
3667        return this

3669    def _replace_lambda(self, node, lambda_variables):
3670        if isinstance(node, exp.Column):
3671            if node.name in lambda_variables:
3672                return node.this
3673        return node

Parser consumes a list of tokens produced by the sqlglot.tokens.Tokenizer and produces a parsed syntax tree.

Args
  • error_level: the desired error level. Default: ErrorLevel.RAISE
  • error_message_context: determines the amount of context to capture from a query string when displaying the error message (in number of characters). Default: 50.
  • index_offset: Index offset for arrays eg ARRAY[0] vs ARRAY[1] as the head of a list. Default: 0
  • alias_post_tablesample: If the table alias comes after tablesample. Default: False
  • max_errors: Maximum number of error messages to include in a raised ParseError. This is only relevant if error_level is ErrorLevel.RAISE. Default: 3
  • null_ordering: Indicates the default null ordering method to use if not explicitly set. Options are "nulls_are_small", "nulls_are_large", "nulls_are_last". Default: "nulls_are_small"

 229    def generate(self, expression: t.Optional[exp.Expression]) -> str:
 230        """
 231        Generates a SQL string by interpreting the given syntax tree.
 232
 233        Args
 234            expression: the syntax tree.
 235
 236        Returns
 237            the SQL string.
 238        """
 239        self.unsupported_messages = []
 240        sql = self.sql(expression).strip()
 241
 242        if self.unsupported_level == ErrorLevel.IGNORE:
 243            return sql
 244
 245        if self.unsupported_level == ErrorLevel.WARN:
 246            for msg in self.unsupported_messages:
 247                logger.warning(msg)
 248        elif self.unsupported_level == ErrorLevel.RAISE and self.unsupported_messages:
 249            raise UnsupportedError(concat_messages(self.unsupported_messages, self.max_unsupported))
 250
 251        if self.pretty:
 252            sql = sql.replace(self.SENTINEL_LINE_BREAK, "\n")
 253        return sql
 254
 255    def unsupported(self, message: str) -> None:
 256        if self.unsupported_level == ErrorLevel.IMMEDIATE:
 257            raise UnsupportedError(message)
 258        self.unsupported_messages.append(message)

 271    def maybe_comment(self, sql: str, expression: exp.Expression) -> str:
 272        comments = expression.comments if self._comments else None
 273
 274        if not comments:
 275            return sql
 276
 277        sep = "\n" if self.pretty else " "
 278        comments_sql = sep.join(
 279            f"/*{self.pad_comment(comment)}*/" for comment in comments if comment
 280        )
 281
 282        if not comments_sql:
 283            return sql
 284
 285        if isinstance(expression, self.WITH_SEPARATED_COMMENTS):
 286            return f"{comments_sql}{self.sep()}{sql}"
 287
 288        return f"{sql} {comments_sql}"

 314    def indent(
 315        self,
 316        sql: str,
 317        level: int = 0,
 318        pad: t.Optional[int] = None,
 319        skip_first: bool = False,
 320        skip_last: bool = False,
 321    ) -> str:
 322        if not self.pretty:
 323            return sql
 324
 325        pad = self.pad if pad is None else pad
 326        lines = sql.split("\n")
 327
 328        return "\n".join(
 329            line
 330            if (skip_first and i == 0) or (skip_last and i == len(lines) - 1)
 331            else f"{' ' * (level * self._indent + pad)}{line}"
 332            for i, line in enumerate(lines)
 333        )

 335    def sql(
 336        self,
 337        expression: t.Optional[str | exp.Expression],
 338        key: t.Optional[str] = None,
 339        comment: bool = True,
 340    ) -> str:
 341        if not expression:
 342            return ""
 343
 344        if isinstance(expression, str):
 345            return expression
 346
 347        if key:
 348            return self.sql(expression.args.get(key))
 349
 350        transform = self.TRANSFORMS.get(expression.__class__)
 351
 352        if callable(transform):
 353            sql = transform(self, expression)
 354        elif transform:
 355            sql = transform
 356        elif isinstance(expression, exp.Expression):
 357            exp_handler_name = f"{expression.key}_sql"
 358
 359            if hasattr(self, exp_handler_name):
 360                sql = getattr(self, exp_handler_name)(expression)
 361            elif isinstance(expression, exp.Func):
 362                sql = self.function_fallback_sql(expression)
 363            elif isinstance(expression, exp.Property):
 364                sql = self.property_sql(expression)
 365            else:
 366                raise ValueError(f"Unsupported expression type {expression.__class__.__name__}")
 367        else:
 368            raise ValueError(f"Expected an Expression. Received {type(expression)}: {expression}")
 369
 370        return self.maybe_comment(sql, expression) if self._comments and comment else sql

 469    def create_sql(self, expression: exp.Create) -> str:
 470        kind = self.sql(expression, "kind").upper()
 471        properties = expression.args.get("properties")
 472        properties_exp = expression.copy()
 473        properties_locs = self.locate_properties(properties) if properties else {}
 474        if properties_locs.get(exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_ROOT) or properties_locs.get(
 475            exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_WITH
 476        ):
 477            properties_exp.set(
 478                "properties",
 479                exp.Properties(
 480                    expressions=[
 481                        *properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_ROOT],
 482                        *properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_WITH],
 483                    ]
 484                ),
 485            )
 486        if kind == "TABLE" and properties_locs.get(exp.Properties.Location.PRE_SCHEMA):
 487            this_name = self.sql(expression.this, "this")
 488            this_properties = self.properties(
 489                exp.Properties(expressions=properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.PRE_SCHEMA]),
 490                wrapped=False,
 491            )
 492            this_schema = f"({self.expressions(expression.this)})"
 493            this = f"{this_name}, {this_properties} {this_schema}"
 494            properties_sql = ""
 495        else:
 496            this = self.sql(expression, "this")
 497            properties_sql = self.sql(properties_exp, "properties")
 498        begin = " BEGIN" if expression.args.get("begin") else ""
 499        expression_sql = self.sql(expression, "expression")
 500        expression_sql = f" AS{begin}{self.sep()}{expression_sql}" if expression_sql else ""
 501        temporary = " TEMPORARY" if expression.args.get("temporary") else ""
 502        transient = (
 503            " TRANSIENT" if self.CREATE_TRANSIENT and expression.args.get("transient") else ""
 504        )
 505        external = " EXTERNAL" if expression.args.get("external") else ""
 506        replace = " OR REPLACE" if expression.args.get("replace") else ""
 507        exists_sql = " IF NOT EXISTS" if expression.args.get("exists") else ""
 508        unique = " UNIQUE" if expression.args.get("unique") else ""
 509        materialized = " MATERIALIZED" if expression.args.get("materialized") else ""
 510        set_ = " SET" if expression.args.get("set") else ""
 511        multiset = " MULTISET" if expression.args.get("multiset") else ""
 512        global_temporary = " GLOBAL TEMPORARY" if expression.args.get("global_temporary") else ""
 513        volatile = " VOLATILE" if expression.args.get("volatile") else ""
 514        data = expression.args.get("data")
 515        if data is None:
 516            data = ""
 517        elif data:
 518            data = " WITH DATA"
 519        else:
 520            data = " WITH NO DATA"
 521        statistics = expression.args.get("statistics")
 522        if statistics is None:
 523            statistics = ""
 524        elif statistics:
 525            statistics = " AND STATISTICS"
 526        else:
 527            statistics = " AND NO STATISTICS"
 528        no_primary_index = " NO PRIMARY INDEX" if expression.args.get("no_primary_index") else ""
 529
 530        indexes = expression.args.get("indexes")
 531        index_sql = ""
 532        if indexes:
 533            indexes_sql = []
 534            for index in indexes:
 535                ind_unique = " UNIQUE" if index.args.get("unique") else ""
 536                ind_primary = " PRIMARY" if index.args.get("primary") else ""
 537                ind_amp = " AMP" if index.args.get("amp") else ""
 538                ind_name = f" {index.name}" if index.name else ""
 539                ind_columns = (
 540                    f' ({self.expressions(index, key="columns", flat=True)})'
 541                    if index.args.get("columns")
 542                    else ""
 543                )
 544                if index.args.get("primary") and properties_locs.get(
 545                    exp.Properties.Location.POST_INDEX
 546                ):
 547                    postindex_props_sql = self.properties(
 548                        exp.Properties(
 549                            expressions=properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.POST_INDEX]
 550                        ),
 551                        wrapped=False,
 552                    )
 553                    ind_columns = f"{ind_columns} {postindex_props_sql}"
 554
 555                indexes_sql.append(
 556                    f"{ind_unique}{ind_primary}{ind_amp} INDEX{ind_name}{ind_columns}"
 557                )
 558            index_sql = "".join(indexes_sql)
 559
 560        postcreate_props_sql = ""
 561        if properties_locs.get(exp.Properties.Location.POST_CREATE):
 562            postcreate_props_sql = self.properties(
 563                exp.Properties(expressions=properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.POST_CREATE]),
 564                sep=" ",
 565                prefix=" ",
 566                wrapped=False,
 567            )
 568
 569        modifiers = "".join(
 570            (
 571                replace,
 572                temporary,
 573                transient,
 574                external,
 575                unique,
 576                materialized,
 577                set_,
 578                multiset,
 579                global_temporary,
 580                volatile,
 581                postcreate_props_sql,
 582            )
 583        )
 584        no_schema_binding = (
 585            " WITH NO SCHEMA BINDING" if expression.args.get("no_schema_binding") else ""
 586        )
 587
 588        post_expression_modifiers = "".join((data, statistics, no_primary_index))
 589
 590        expression_sql = f"CREATE{modifiers} {kind}{exists_sql} {this}{properties_sql}{expression_sql}{post_expression_modifiers}{index_sql}{no_schema_binding}"
 591        return self.prepend_ctes(expression, expression_sql)
 592
 593    def describe_sql(self, expression: exp.Describe) -> str:
 594        return f"DESCRIBE {self.sql(expression, 'this')}"

 596    def prepend_ctes(self, expression: exp.Expression, sql: str) -> str:
 597        with_ = self.sql(expression, "with")
 598        if with_:
 599            sql = f"{with_}{self.sep()}{sql}"
 600        return sql

 624    def datatype_sql(self, expression: exp.DataType) -> str:
 625        type_value = expression.this
 626        type_sql = self.TYPE_MAPPING.get(type_value, type_value.value)
 627        nested = ""
 628        interior = self.expressions(expression, flat=True)
 629        values = ""
 630        if interior:
 631            if expression.args.get("nested"):
 632                nested = f"{self.STRUCT_DELIMITER[0]}{interior}{self.STRUCT_DELIMITER[1]}"
 633                if expression.args.get("values") is not None:
 634                    delimiters = ("[", "]") if type_value == exp.DataType.Type.ARRAY else ("(", ")")
 635                    values = (
 636                        f"{delimiters[0]}{self.expressions(expression, 'values')}{delimiters[1]}"
 637                    )
 638            else:
 639                nested = f"({interior})"
 640
 641        return f"{type_sql}{nested}{values}"

 715    def properties_sql(self, expression: exp.Properties) -> str:
 716        root_properties = []
 717        with_properties = []
 718
 719        for p in expression.expressions:
 720            p_loc = self.PROPERTIES_LOCATION[p.__class__]
 721            if p_loc == exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_WITH:
 722                with_properties.append(p)
 723            elif p_loc == exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_ROOT:
 724                root_properties.append(p)
 725
 726        return self.root_properties(
 727            exp.Properties(expressions=root_properties)
 728        ) + self.with_properties(exp.Properties(expressions=with_properties))
 729
 730    def root_properties(self, properties: exp.Properties) -> str:
 731        if properties.expressions:
 732            return self.sep() + self.expressions(properties, indent=False, sep=" ")
 733        return ""

 735    def properties(
 736        self,
 737        properties: exp.Properties,
 738        prefix: str = "",
 739        sep: str = ", ",
 740        suffix: str = "",
 741        wrapped: bool = True,
 742    ) -> str:
 743        if properties.expressions:
 744            expressions = self.expressions(properties, sep=sep, indent=False)
 745            expressions = self.wrap(expressions) if wrapped else expressions
 746            return f"{prefix}{' ' if prefix and prefix != ' ' else ''}{expressions}{suffix}"
 747        return ""
 748
 749    def with_properties(self, properties: exp.Properties) -> str:
 750        return self.properties(properties, prefix=self.seg("WITH"))
 751
 752    def locate_properties(
 753        self, properties: exp.Properties
 754    ) -> t.Dict[exp.Properties.Location, list[exp.Property]]:
 755        properties_locs: t.Dict[exp.Properties.Location, list[exp.Property]] = {
 756            key: [] for key in exp.Properties.Location
 757        }
 758
 759        for p in properties.expressions:
 760            p_loc = self.PROPERTIES_LOCATION[p.__class__]
 761            if p_loc == exp.Properties.Location.PRE_SCHEMA:
 762                properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.PRE_SCHEMA].append(p)
 763            elif p_loc == exp.Properties.Location.POST_INDEX:
 764                properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.POST_INDEX].append(p)
 765            elif p_loc == exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_ROOT:
 766                properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_ROOT].append(p)
 767            elif p_loc == exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_WITH:
 768                properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.POST_SCHEMA_WITH].append(p)
 769            elif p_loc == exp.Properties.Location.POST_CREATE:
 770                properties_locs[exp.Properties.Location.POST_CREATE].append(p)
 771            elif p_loc == exp.Properties.Location.UNSUPPORTED:
 772                self.unsupported(f"Unsupported property {p.key}")
 773
 774        return properties_locs

 776    def property_sql(self, expression: exp.Property) -> str:
 777        property_cls = expression.__class__
 778        if property_cls == exp.Property:
 779            return f"{expression.name}={self.sql(expression, 'value')}"
 780
 781        property_name = exp.Properties.PROPERTY_TO_NAME.get(property_cls)
 782        if not property_name:
 783            self.unsupported(f"Unsupported property {expression.key}")
 784
 785        return f"{property_name}={self.sql(expression, 'this')}"

 932    def table_sql(self, expression: exp.Table, sep: str = " AS ") -> str:
 933        table = ".".join(
 934            part
 935            for part in [
 936                self.sql(expression, "catalog"),
 937                self.sql(expression, "db"),
 938                self.sql(expression, "this"),
 939            ]
 940            if part
 941        )
 942
 943        alias = self.sql(expression, "alias")
 944        alias = f"{sep}{alias}" if alias else ""
 945        hints = self.expressions(expression, key="hints", sep=", ", flat=True)
 946        hints = f" WITH ({hints})" if hints else ""
 947        laterals = self.expressions(expression, key="laterals", sep="")
 948        joins = self.expressions(expression, key="joins", sep="")
 949        pivots = self.expressions(expression, key="pivots", sep="")
 950        system_time = expression.args.get("system_time")
 951        system_time = f" {self.sql(expression, 'system_time')}" if system_time else ""
 952
 953        if alias and pivots:
 954            pivots = f"{pivots}{alias}"
 955            alias = ""
 956
 957        return f"{table}{system_time}{alias}{hints}{laterals}{joins}{pivots}"
 958
 959    def tablesample_sql(self, expression: exp.TableSample) -> str:
 960        if self.alias_post_tablesample and expression.this.alias:
 961            this = self.sql(expression.this, "this")
 962            alias = f" AS {self.sql(expression.this, 'alias')}"
 963        else:
 964            this = self.sql(expression, "this")
 965            alias = ""
 966        method = self.sql(expression, "method")
 967        method = f" {method.upper()} " if method else ""
 968        numerator = self.sql(expression, "bucket_numerator")
 969        denominator = self.sql(expression, "bucket_denominator")
 970        field = self.sql(expression, "bucket_field")
 971        field = f" ON {field}" if field else ""
 972        bucket = f"BUCKET {numerator} OUT OF {denominator}{field}" if numerator else ""
 973        percent = self.sql(expression, "percent")
 974        percent = f"{percent} PERCENT" if percent else ""
 975        rows = self.sql(expression, "rows")
 976        rows = f"{rows} ROWS" if rows else ""
 977        size = self.sql(expression, "size")
 978        seed = self.sql(expression, "seed")
 979        seed = f" SEED ({seed})" if seed else ""
 980        return f"{this} TABLESAMPLE{method}({bucket}{percent}{rows}{size}){seed}{alias}"

1024    def group_sql(self, expression: exp.Group) -> str:
1025        group_by = self.op_expressions("GROUP BY", expression)
1026        grouping_sets = self.expressions(expression, key="grouping_sets", indent=False)
1027        grouping_sets = (
1028            f"{self.seg('GROUPING SETS')} {self.wrap(grouping_sets)}" if grouping_sets else ""
1029        )

1031        cube = expression.args.get("cube")
1032        if cube is True:
1033            cube = self.seg("WITH CUBE")
1034        else:
1035            cube = self.expressions(expression, key="cube", indent=False)
1036            cube = f"{self.seg('CUBE')} {self.wrap(cube)}" if cube else ""
1037
1038        rollup = expression.args.get("rollup")
1039        if rollup is True:
1040            rollup = self.seg("WITH ROLLUP")
1041        else:
1042            rollup = self.expressions(expression, key="rollup", indent=False)
1043            rollup = f"{self.seg('ROLLUP')} {self.wrap(rollup)}" if rollup else ""
1044
1045        return f"{group_by}{csv(grouping_sets, cube, rollup, sep=',')}"
1046
1047    def having_sql(self, expression: exp.Having) -> str:
1048        this = self.indent(self.sql(expression, "this"))
1049        return f"{self.seg('HAVING')}{self.sep()}{this}"
1050
1051    def join_sql(self, expression: exp.Join) -> str:
1052        op_sql = self.seg(
1053            " ".join(
1054                op
1055                for op in (
1056                    "NATURAL" if expression.args.get("natural") else None,
1057                    expression.side,
1058                    expression.kind,
1059                    "JOIN",
1060                )
1061                if op
1062            )
1063        )
1064        on_sql = self.sql(expression, "on")
1065        using = expression.args.get("using")
1066
1067        if not on_sql and using:
1068            on_sql = csv(*(self.sql(column) for column in using))
1069
1070        if on_sql:
1071            on_sql = self.indent(on_sql, skip_first=True)
1072            space = self.seg(" " * self.pad) if self.pretty else " "
1073            if using:
1074                on_sql = f"{space}USING ({on_sql})"
1075            else:
1076                on_sql = f"{space}ON {on_sql}"
1077
1078        expression_sql = self.sql(expression, "expression")
1079        this_sql = self.sql(expression, "this")
1080        return f"{expression_sql}{op_sql} {this_sql}{on_sql}"
1081
1082    def lambda_sql(self, expression: exp.Lambda, arrow_sep: str = "->") -> str:
1083        args = self.expressions(expression, flat=True)
1084        args = f"({args})" if len(args.split(",")) > 1 else args
1085        return f"{args} {arrow_sep} {self.sql(expression, 'this')}"

1087    def lateral_sql(self, expression: exp.Lateral) -> str:
1088        this = self.sql(expression, "this")
1089
1090        if isinstance(expression.this, exp.Subquery):
1091            return f"LATERAL {this}"
1092
1093        if expression.args.get("view"):
1094            alias = expression.args["alias"]
1095            columns = self.expressions(alias, key="columns", flat=True)
1096            table = f" {alias.name}" if alias.name else ""
1097            columns = f" AS {columns}" if columns else ""
1098            op_sql = self.seg(f"LATERAL VIEW{' OUTER' if expression.args.get('outer') else ''}")
1099            return f"{op_sql}{self.sep()}{this}{table}{columns}"
1100
1101        alias = self.sql(expression, "alias")
1102        alias = f" AS {alias}" if alias else ""
1103        return f"LATERAL {this}{alias}"

1113    def lock_sql(self, expression: exp.Lock) -> str:

1115            lock_type = "UPDATE" if expression.args["update"] else "SHARE"
1116            return self.seg(f"FOR {lock_type}")

1121    def literal_sql(self, expression: exp.Literal) -> str:
1122        text = expression.this or ""
1123        if expression.is_string:
1124            if self._replace_backslash:
1125                text = text.replace("\\", "\\\\")
1126            text = text.replace(self.quote_end, self._escaped_quote_end)
1127            if self.pretty:
1128                text = text.replace("\n", self.SENTINEL_LINE_BREAK)
1129            text = f"{self.quote_start}{text}{self.quote_end}"
1130        return text

1165    def ordered_sql(self, expression: exp.Ordered) -> str:
1166        desc = expression.args.get("desc")
1167        asc = not desc
1168
1169        nulls_first = expression.args.get("nulls_first")
1170        nulls_last = not nulls_first
1171        nulls_are_large = self.null_ordering == "nulls_are_large"
1172        nulls_are_small = self.null_ordering == "nulls_are_small"
1173        nulls_are_last = self.null_ordering == "nulls_are_last"
1174
1175        sort_order = " DESC" if desc else ""
1176        nulls_sort_change = ""
1177        if nulls_first and (
1178            (asc and nulls_are_large) or (desc and nulls_are_small) or nulls_are_last
1179        ):
1180            nulls_sort_change = " NULLS FIRST"
1181        elif (
1182            nulls_last
1183            and ((asc and nulls_are_small) or (desc and nulls_are_large))
1184            and not nulls_are_last
1185        ):
1186            nulls_sort_change = " NULLS LAST"
1187
1188        if nulls_sort_change and not self.NULL_ORDERING_SUPPORTED:
1189            self.unsupported(
1190                "Sorting in an ORDER BY on NULLS FIRST/NULLS LAST is not supported by this dialect"
1191            )
1192            nulls_sort_change = ""
1193
1194        return f"{self.sql(expression, 'this')}{sort_order}{nulls_sort_change}"

1196    def matchrecognize_sql(self, expression: exp.MatchRecognize) -> str:
1197        partition = self.partition_by_sql(expression)
1198        order = self.sql(expression, "order")
1199        measures = self.sql(expression, "measures")
1200        measures = self.seg(f"MEASURES {measures}") if measures else ""
1201        rows = self.sql(expression, "rows")
1202        rows = self.seg(rows) if rows else ""
1203        after = self.sql(expression, "after")
1204        after = self.seg(after) if after else ""
1205        pattern = self.sql(expression, "pattern")
1206        pattern = self.seg(f"PATTERN ({pattern})") if pattern else ""
1207        define = self.sql(expression, "define")
1208        define = self.seg(f"DEFINE {define}") if define else ""
1209        body = "".join(
1210            (
1211                partition,
1212                order,
1213                measures,
1214                rows,
1215                after,
1216                pattern,
1217                define,
1218            )
1219        )
1220        return f"{self.seg('MATCH_RECOGNIZE')} {self.wrap(body)}"

1222    def query_modifiers(self, expression: exp.Expression, *sqls: str) -> str:
1223        return csv(
1224            *sqls,
1225            *[self.sql(sql) for sql in expression.args.get("joins") or []],
1226            self.sql(expression, "match"),
1227            *[self.sql(sql) for sql in expression.args.get("laterals") or []],
1228            self.sql(expression, "where"),
1229            self.sql(expression, "group"),
1230            self.sql(expression, "having"),
1231            self.sql(expression, "qualify"),
1232            self.seg("WINDOW ") + self.expressions(expression, "windows", flat=True)
1233            if expression.args.get("windows")
1234            else "",
1235            self.sql(expression, "distribute"),
1236            self.sql(expression, "sort"),
1237            self.sql(expression, "cluster"),
1238            self.sql(expression, "order"),
1239            self.sql(expression, "limit"),
1240            self.sql(expression, "offset"),
1241            self.sql(expression, "lock"),
1242            sep="",
1243        )

1251        sql = self.query_modifiers(

1315    def unnest_sql(self, expression: exp.Unnest) -> str:

1321        else:

1333    def window_sql(self, expression: exp.Window) -> str:
1334        this = self.sql(expression, "this")
1335
1336        partition = self.partition_by_sql(expression)
1337
1338        order = expression.args.get("order")
1339        order_sql = self.order_sql(order, flat=True) if order else ""
1340
1341        partition_sql = partition + " " if partition and order else partition
1342
1343        spec = expression.args.get("spec")
1344        spec_sql = " " + self.window_spec_sql(spec) if spec else ""
1345
1346        alias = self.sql(expression, "alias")
1347        this = f"{this} {'AS' if expression.arg_key == 'windows' else 'OVER'}"
1348
1349        if not partition and not order and not spec and alias:
1350            return f"{this} {alias}"
1351
1352        window_args = alias + partition_sql + order_sql + spec_sql
1353
1354        return f"{this} ({window_args.strip()})"

1395    def case_sql(self, expression: exp.Case) -> str:
1396        this = self.sql(expression, "this")
1397        statements = [f"CASE {this}" if this else "CASE"]
1398
1399        for e in expression.args["ifs"]:
1400            statements.append(f"WHEN {self.sql(e, 'this')}")
1401            statements.append(f"THEN {self.sql(e, 'true')}")
1402
1403        default = self.sql(expression, "default")
1404
1405        if default:
1406            statements.append(f"ELSE {default}")
1407
1408        statements.append("END")
1409
1410        if self.pretty and self.text_width(statements) > self._max_text_width:
1411            return self.indent("\n".join(statements), skip_first=True, skip_last=True)
1412
1413        return " ".join(statements)

1784    def expressions(
1785        self,
1786        expression: exp.Expression,
1787        key: t.Optional[str] = None,
1788        flat: bool = False,
1789        indent: bool = True,
1790        sep: str = ", ",
1791        prefix: str = "",

1795        if not expressions:

1798        if flat:
1799            return sep.join(self.sql(e) for e in expressions)
1800
1801        num_sqls = len(expressions)
1802
1803        # These are calculated once in case we have the leading_comma / pretty option set, correspondingly
1804        pad = " " * self.pad
1805        stripped_sep = sep.strip()
1806
1807        result_sqls = []
1808        for i, e in enumerate(expressions):
1809            sql = self.sql(e, comment=False)
1810            comments = self.maybe_comment("", e) if isinstance(e, exp.Expression) else ""

1812            if self.pretty:
1813                if self._leading_comma:
1814                    result_sqls.append(f"{sep if i > 0 else pad}{prefix}{sql}{comments}")
1815                else:
1816                    result_sqls.append(
1817                        f"{prefix}{sql}{stripped_sep if i + 1 < num_sqls else ''}{comments}"
1818                    )
1819            else:
1820                result_sqls.append(f"{prefix}{sql}{comments}{sep if i + 1 < num_sqls else ''}")
1821
1822        result_sql = "\n".join(result_sqls) if self.pretty else "".join(result_sqls)
1823        return self.indent(result_sql, skip_first=False) if indent else result_sql

Generator interprets the given syntax tree and produces a SQL string as an output.

Args
  • time_mapping (dict): the dictionary of custom time mappings in which the key represents a python time format and the output the target time format
  • time_trie (trie): a trie of the time_mapping keys
  • pretty (bool): if set to True the returned string will be formatted. Default: False.
  • quote_start (str): specifies which starting character to use to delimit quotes. Default: '.
  • quote_end (str): specifies which ending character to use to delimit quotes. Default: '.
  • identifier_start (str): specifies which starting character to use to delimit identifiers. Default: ".
  • identifier_end (str): specifies which ending character to use to delimit identifiers. Default: ".
  • identify (bool): if set to True all identifiers will be delimited by the corresponding character.
  • normalize (bool): if set to True all identifiers will lower cased
  • escape (str): specifies an escape character. Default: '.
  • pad (int): determines padding in a formatted string. Default: 2.
  • indent (int): determines the size of indentation in a formatted string. Default: 4.
  • unnest_column_only (bool): if true unnest table aliases are considered only as column aliases
  • normalize_functions (str): normalize function names, "upper", "lower", or None Default: "upper"
  • alias_post_tablesample (bool): if the table alias comes after tablesample Default: False
  • unsupported_level (ErrorLevel): determines the generator's behavior when it encounters unsupported expressions. Default ErrorLevel.WARN.
  • null_ordering (str): Indicates the default null ordering method to use if not explicitly set. Options are "nulls_are_small", "nulls_are_large", "nulls_are_last". Default: "nulls_are_small"
  • max_unsupported (int): Maximum number of unsupported messages to include in a raised UnsupportedError. This is only relevant if unsupported_level is ErrorLevel.RAISE. Default: 3
  • leading_comma (bool): if the the comma is leading or trailing in select statements Default: False
  • max_text_width: The max number of characters in a segment before creating new lines in pretty mode. The default is on the smaller end because the length only represents a segment and not the true line length. Default: 80
  • comments: Whether or not to preserve comments in the output SQL code. Default: True

310        return f"{map_func_name}({self.format_args(keys, values)})"
311
312    args = []
313    for key, value in zip(keys.expressions, values.expressions):
314        args.append(self.sql(key))
315        args.append(self.sql(value))
316    return f"{map_func_name}({self.format_args(*args)})"

def create_with_partitions_sql(self, expression): 
339def create_with_partitions_sql(self, expression):
340    """
341    In Hive and Spark, the PARTITIONED BY property acts as an extension of a table's schema. When the
342    PARTITIONED BY value is an array of column names, they are transformed into a schema. The corresponding
343    columns are removed from the create statement.
344    """
345    has_schema = isinstance(expression.this, exp.Schema)
346    is_partitionable = expression.args.get("kind") in ("TABLE", "VIEW")
347
348    if has_schema and is_partitionable:
349        expression = expression.copy()
350        prop = expression.find(exp.PartitionedByProperty)
351        this = prop and prop.this
352        if prop and not isinstance(this, exp.Schema):
353            schema = expression.this
354            columns = {v.name.upper() for v in this.expressions}
355            partitions = [col for col in schema.expressions if col.name.upper() in columns]
356            schema.set("expressions", [e for e in schema.expressions if e not in partitions])
357            prop.replace(exp.PartitionedByProperty(this=exp.Schema(expressions=partitions)))
358            expression.set("this", schema)
359
360    return self.create_sql(expression)

def trim_sql(self, expression): 
398def trim_sql(self, expression):
399    target = self.sql(expression, "this")
400    trim_type = self.sql(expression, "position")
401    remove_chars = self.sql(expression, "expression")
402    collation = self.sql(expression, "collation")
403
404    # Use TRIM/LTRIM/RTRIM syntax if the expression isn't database-specific
405    if not remove_chars and not collation:
406        return self.trim_sql(expression)
407
408    trim_type = f"{trim_type} " if trim_type else ""
409    remove_chars = f"{remove_chars} " if remove_chars else ""
410    from_part = "FROM " if trim_type or remove_chars else ""
411    collation = f" COLLATE {collation}" if collation else ""
412    return f"TRIM({trim_type}{remove_chars}{from_part}{target}{collation})"
